		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Balto.</placeName> <date>Sept. 10 5608</date></p>
				<p>My dear Friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><add>Hebrew</add> and thank you for it.  We<lb/> only wish to have the form of the Inscription usual with you<lb/> was that I should make it as simple as possible.  In <persName>Mr<lb/> Wolfries<add>&#63;</add></persName> I have copies of a great many on the tombs in<lb/> some off&#45;cities in <placeName>Germany</placeName>&#44; and they are interesting&#44;<lb/> I don&#39;t know whether you have this old work of his<lb/> it is interesting and is a wonderful <add>&#63;</add> here.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have duly boted<add>&#63;</add> your advice in regards to the<lb/> Lady in question.  I do not know her &#40;except a mere bow<lb/> when I meet her with her friends &#38; then <sic>recognise</sic> her&#41;<lb/> but if I understand her character truly&#44; in these days<lb/> of homeopathy&#44; when <hi rend="underline"><add>&#63;</add> <add>&#63;</add></hi> &#38;c rules every<lb/> thing she would not suit me <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; and how<lb/> much better the <add>&#63;</add> so towards yourself and or re&#61;<lb/>paid the talents&#44; <add>Hebrew</add> by common consent.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You were kind enough to quote me a sentence from<lb/> our learned Fathers to support your good advice &#38;c&#44; but<lb/> how imperative is the change upon you when you re&#45;<lb/>collect the conclusion of the sentence which you seem</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>to have forgotten&#58; <add>Hebrew</add> so I hope you will<lb/> still have this letter in <add>&#63;</add> <add>Hebrew</add> which you may<lb/> choose to be <add>&#63;</add> in preference&#44; you have at last<lb/> come to the conclusion to which long since I had come<lb/> to be satisfied &#38; content with what ever presents itself.  I<lb/> find after all this is the <add>&#63;</add> secret in life.  <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> <add>Hebrew</add>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In the last <sic>occident</sic> you review&#8212;Hebrew and<lb/> English vocabulary I speak well of it&#8212;I was thinking of<lb/> such a look only a day or two before your no came for<lb/> our little children&#8212;and as you have been very kind<lb/> in loaning me your books from time to time&#44; can you<lb/> spare me this that I may see whether it is worth while<lb/> to send for a copy.  <persName>Rev. I.</persName> who will take this on&#44; will<lb/> take charge of it.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I do not remember whether I wrote<lb/> you in acknowledgment about <persName>Eddy&#39;s</persName> names which <persName>Rabbi I.</persName> says he has as<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add>&#8212;how we should have selected this name&#44; I know<lb/> not&#44; and am rather inclined to think there is some<lb/> mistake.  Bro. I. propose to see him&#8212;the name is good<lb/> enough and it is classical.  I do not mean however&#44; Bibli&#45;<lb/>cal&#8212;but how this should have selected I know not.</p>
				<p>&#40;as already said&#41;<lb/>  all well with us&#8212;we expect</p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p>our wanderer home tomorrow&#44; or next day after a long &#38;<lb/> pleasant sojourn at <placeName>Newport</placeName> &#38;c.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Unless you come on to <placeName>Balt.</placeName> soon&#44; we shall<lb/> not see you for a long time I fear&#44; as the Holydays are<lb/> approaching.  By the way <persName>Mr Rice</persName> told me on <date>Friday</date><lb/> that the new synagogue was to be consecrated <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> won&#39;t you be here&#63;</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">With <add>&#63;</add> regard</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">your friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">Joshua I. Cohen</persName></p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Rev. Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>371 Walnut St</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p><add>&#63;</add></p>
